<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 94 / P&amp;O to withdraw Chinese workers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD DONKIN, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
P&amp;O European Ferries bowed to pressure from French seafaring unions
yesterday and agreed to withdraw 58 Chinese cleaners from its two most
recently chartered ferries.
The French unions disrupted dockings at Cherbourg last week and spread the
action yesterday to Calais, although P&amp;O had already said it would dispense
with the Chinese workers.
The government yesterday asked the French government to intervene in the
dispute after French workers blocked the departure of a P&amp;O ferry from
Calais, disrupting sailings for several hours.
The dispute arose when the French seafarers complained that employment of
the Chinese could drive down pay for other nationalities. However, P&amp;O
suggested yesterday that the action had been a smokescreen for wider fears
about French ferry jobs.
The two ships in which the Chinese were employed were previously run by the
German Olau line.
</TEXT>
