<HEADLINE>
FT  09 JUN 94 / Pizza Hut plans to expand by 20%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Pizza Hut, the restaurant and fast-food chain, said yesterday it intended to
open more than 40 restaurants and 60 delivery units throughout the country
over the next two years - a 20 per cent increase - creating up to 2,000
jobs.
It is seeking town-centre sites, free-standing units in out-of-town retail
parks and delivery units in high streets and other locations.
The number of pizza restaurants is rising by about 12 per cent a year with
delivery outlets - the fastest-growing sector - increasing by about 30 per
cent a year.
