FT  09 JUN 94 / Housing market sales up 25%
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The total number of transactions in the housing market increased by 25 per
cent in the six months to March compared with the same period in the
previous year, says a report by the Valuation Office, an agency of the
Inland Revenue.
House prices rose by an average of 0.66 per cent over the six months,
according to district valuers.
The performance of different regions ranged from no movement in the
north-west, south-west and west Midlands to a 2 per cent rise in the east
Midlands.
Residential building land values increased sharply in areas such as East
Anglia, where they rose by 15 per cent. The west Midlands, the north of
England, and Wales registered only minimal rises in average values.
