FT  09 JUN 94 / P&amp;O to withdraw Chinese workers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RICHARD DONKIN, Labour Staff
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
P&amp;O European Ferries bowed to pressure from French seafaring unions
yesterday and agreed to withdraw 58 Chinese cleaners on its two most
recently chartered ferries.
The French unions had disrupted dockings at Cherbourg last week and spread
the action yesterday to Calais, although P&amp;O had already said it would
dispense with the Chinese workers.
The government yesterday asked the French government to intervene in the
dispute after French workers blocked the departure of a P&amp;O ferry from
Calais, disrupting sailings for several hours.
The dispute arose when the French seafarers complained that employment of
the Chinese could drive down pay for other nationals. However, P&amp;O suggested
yesterday that the action had been a smokescreen for wider fears about
French ferry jobs.
The company said it was reluctantly ending the employment of the Chinese on
the two ships, which were previously run by Germany's Olau line.
It added: 'Chinese have served on these two ships for the past four years
while they were operating between the UK and the Netherlands under a German
flag.'
The company said it was examining the legal implications of the action.
</TEXT>
