<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 94 / London Stock Exchange: Switching activity in Hanson
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By STEVE THOMPSON, CHRISTINE BUCKLEY and CLARE GASCOIGNE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Hanson warrants and ordinary shares figured prominently in the market's most
actively traded stocks, with the Seaq ticker revealing two exceptionally
heavy deals in the warrants and one big trade in the ordinary shares.
Turnover of 11m Hanson warrants was almost entirely due to two trades, each
of 5m warrants carried out at 32p apiece, while Hanson ordinary saw turnover
of 7.5m shares, with 3m accounted for by a single trade at 253 1/2p. Salomon
Brothers, the US brokerage, acknowledged that it had been heavily involved
in a switching operation. Hanson ordinary closed 3 3/4 off at 250 3/4p and
the warrants lost a penny at 31 1/2p.
</TEXT>
