<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 94 / UK Company News: Ingham at Pounds 1.9m and plans car parts
growth
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Ingham, the York-based motor parts, worsted spinning and property group,
reported profits of Pounds 1.91m for the year to March 31 on turnover of
Pounds 25.3m.
The car parts division contributed profits of Pounds 1.47m and turnover of
Pounds 19.2m despite the recession and a move to wholesale sales which cut
margins.
The company is seeking to expand the division through acquisitions.
In the previous period, for the 15 months to March 31 1993, group profits
were Pounds 838,000 on turnover of Pounds 11.2m. However, the two companies
making up the parts division were not acquired until September 1992 and May
1993.
The company said the spinning company enjoyed a much better year and
property was showing signs of improvement.
Earnings per share were 8.2p (8.9p). A proposed final dividend of 3.25p
makes a 5p total, against 6p for 15 months.
</TEXT>
