<HEADLINE>
FT  08 JUN 94 / People: Non-executive directors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir Marcus Fox, 66, Tory MP and chairman of the party's 1922 committee, has
joined the board of Pubmaster, the pub retailing arm of the heavily-indebted
Brent Walker group.
Sir Marcus' appointment as a non-executive director is a further sign that
one of Britain's biggest pub-owners is likely to be floated on the stock
market over the next year or two. Last year it made operating profits of
Pounds 11.1m on sales of Pounds 100m. Pubmaster chairman John Brackenbury,
58, said that Sir Marcus has an impressive track record in industry as well
as in politics.
