FT  08 JUN 94 / Pounds 232,000 fine over securities selling
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NORMA COHEN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Securities regulators have fined David Coakley, a private client futures and
options firm, and its directors and employees a total of Pounds 232,000 for
using high-pressure sales tactics to sell to unsophisticated investors and
for 'churning' client accounts to gain commission, Norma Cohen writes.
Additional payments towards regulators' costs and client compensation brings
the total charges to Pounds 276,160.
The Securities and Futures Authority, which last year ordered the firm to
close, said that a disciplinary tribunal hearing had concluded that the
pattern of its activities were 'discreditable, reckless and scandalous'.
The firm was fined Pounds 100,000 and Mr David Coakley, its sole director,
was fined Pounds 50,000 and expelled from SFA registers. Mr Stewart Blake,
head of dealing was fined Pounds 30,000 and expelled from SFA registers.
Five account executives were fined amounts ranging from Pounds 20,000 to
Pounds 4,000.
