FT  07 JUN 94 / World Trade News: BAe wins Colombia jet order
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL BETTS, Aerospace Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
British Aerospace yesterday won a Dollars 230m (Pounds 153.3m) order for
regional jets from Colombia and confirmed it was discussing a possible
regional aircraft link-up with Fokker, the Dutch aircraft group controlled
by Deutsche Aerospace.
The Colombian deal involves an order for BAe's regional jet division, Avro
International, for eight RJ100 Avroliners from Colombia's Sociedad
Aeronautica de Medelln Consolidada.
Confirmation of talks between BAe and Deutsche Aerospace over a possible
link with Fokker reflects the efforts of the European industry to
rationalise regional jet business.
BAe said no decision had been made on a possible link-up with Fokker. The
British company is also discussing an alliance in the turbopropeller
regional aircraft sector with Aerospatiale of France.
