<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUN 94 / Spain backs military air project
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By QUENTIN PEEL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SCHWERIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The Spanish government yesterday expressed its firm interest in
participating in the development of a new generation European military
transport aircraft, the so-called Future Large Aircraft. Mr Julian
Garcia-Vargas, Spanish defence minister, told Mr Volker Ruhe, his German
counterpart, that Europe should draw on the experience both of the Airbus
consortium and the Eurofighter project in building the FLA. The Eurofighter
project, he said, showed the disadvantage of increasing costs when the
participating countries reduced their orders. The Spanish interest in the
FLA project will raise the pressure on the British government to decide on
its own participation. Hitherto, Britain has favoured buying Hercules
aircraft from the US for its next phase of military transport needs but
British Aerospace is anxious to be involved in the European project, to
which both Germany and France have committed themselves.
