<HEADLINE>
FT  07 JUN 94 / World Commodities Prices: Tea
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Tea Broker's Association reports strong demand. Bright East Africans
were often dearer while mediums and plainer Central Africans remained fully
firm. Ceylons met good competition but prices were barely steady. Bright
Zimbabwes sold well and gained 5 to 10 pence, others were unchanged. Ceylons
met selective enquiry at irregularly easier rates. Quotations best
available, 230p/kg nom, good 160p/kg, good medium 138p/kg, medium 118p/kg,
low medium 85p/kg. The highest price realised this week was 231p for a
Rwanda pf. 1
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P0831 Forest Products.
